						               													<description>The Netflix TV series that captivated millions of viewers has just become an exciting board game so you can experience the emotions and vicissitudes of the most famous band of thieves of all time.&amp;#10; The game contains: a layout board of the Spanish Mint, 5 screens for hiding your notes from opponents, 1 pad of sheets for jotting down clues, 5 hostage pawns and 8 robber tiles.&amp;#10; With the 44 cards in the game, the players/detectives must discover the identities of the 8 robbers, jotting down the Clues, Confidential Information and Characteristics emerging during the game.&amp;#10; A deduction game in which you must work to reveal the identities of the thieves just like real detectives!&amp;#10; A game that never ceases to amaze match after match, engaging everyone, not only fans of the series, in a fascinating, in-depth and first-hand investigation through a unique recreational experience.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn the professor will call the police and you can reach a different room in the Mint. Here you can check a number of clue depending on the turn you are playing but the thief will be stressed by you and if they go &amp;quot;out of control&amp;quot; they will modify the quantity of the symbols in the room.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To deduct the identity of the wight thieves you'll need to understand which of the three symbols is the most present in each room.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
